        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks HWB for references.</p> 
<p>Praises his paper ["Contributions to an insect fauna of the Amazon valley", read before Linnean Society, 21 Nov 1861, <hi rend="italic">Trans. Linn. Soc. Lond.</hi> 23 (1862) : 495–566] which solves "one of the most perplexing problems which could be given to solve".</p>  
<p>Discusses the difficulties of writing and expresses disappointment at Wallace’s book [<hi rend="italic">Travels on the Amazon</hi> (1861)].</p> 
        </abstract>
